// Iran Crisis
- Protests enter 16th day; 2,000+ killed, 1,200+ detained across 153+ cities; regime blackout on internet/cell service; using foreign jihadists (Afghan, Syrian, Iraqi) for suppression.
- US options: Military strikes under consideration; 25% tariffs imposed on nations trading with Iran; diplomacy explored; opposition leader Reza Pahlavi signals global aid incoming.

// Venezuela Situation
- Maduro captured; acting president Delcy Rodriguez to meet you/oil execs; oil cutoff to Cuba; Big Oil notes revival challenges.
- US ops: 32 Cuban guards killed; Russia counters oil claims; militias hunt US citizens; potential land ops vs. cartels.

// Domestic Security - Immigration/ICE
- Minnesota/Illinois sue over agent surge (2,000+ deployed, 1,000+ arrests); fatal shooting of Renee Good probed by FBI; protests chant threats vs. officials.
- 4 migrants dead in custody; broader ops target fraud/violent charges.

// Economic/Financial Threats
- Fed probe: Global bankers back Powell; inflation at 2.7%; markets hit records but yen/dollar volatile.
- Tariffs: 25% on Iran traders; Vietnam envoy targets trade gap; EU-Mercosur pact limits US leverage.

//Arctic/Greenland Tensions
- Denmark orders "shoot first" vs. US forces; EU offers defense aid; NATO discusses Arctic security; Rubio briefs it's negotiation tactic.

// Middle East/Syria Conflicts
- Gaza: 6 dead in rains; Hamas elects new leader.
- Syria: US ISIS strikes; joint intel hub with Israel; al-Jolani clashes vs. Kurds ongoing.

// Cyber/Tech Risks
- Grok AI probed for deepfakes; Malaysia/Indonesia block it.

// Other Threats
- Terror: Al-Qaeda arrests in Turkey (US embassy targets); ISIS training in US; synagogue arson in Mississippi.
- Global: Myanmar elections; Niger jihadist blockade; drone tanker hits in Black Sea.
